RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROYAL JUBILEE set the pace in the two path, settled back when FUNTASTICA became intent on the lead early on the backstretch, re-bid in the three path rounding the far turn, regained command near the five-sixteenths pole, drew clear in upper stretch and held safe under a steady drive. STUCK IN MALIBU raced off the pace three wide, advanced under urging four wide around the far turn, had aim outside of the winner throughout the stretch run but was only able to gain mildly on the winner. MAJOR PRYCE raced in range three and four wide, shifted in in upper stretch and lacked the needed rally. DULCE AMBICION raced well back three and four wide and had a mild gain outside. FUNTASTICA fought rating in the four path around the first turn, took the lead early on the backstretch, cleared soon after, set the pace in the two path to the five-sixteenths marker and gave way. UPSTREET threw his head at the start, chased pace in the two path and had little left for the drive.
